<kml>
<concept name=Protein-Binding-Site>

<superconcept name=Region><hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Protein-Binding-Site>
  <definition> <conceptref name=Region> on the surface of a protein - typically a                          cavity or groove - that is complementary in <conceptref name=shape> to                           another molecule (the ligand) and therefore can bind it                          through the formation of multiple weak (noncovalent)                          bonds. Alberts:ECB:G-3. </definition>
<seealso name=Nucleic-Acid-Region>
<seealso name=Protein-Region>
<seealso name=Binding-Site>
<seealso name=Atomic-Region>
<seealso name=Regulatory-Region>

</component></kml>
